< Review>
When this place was in Terminal 2, it was much swankier. Now it‚Äôs a bit more cramped and lacking showers and space to spread out but that doesn‚Äôt mean it‚Äôs bad. Some of the nicest people work here and make you feel welcomed and invited. They keep the drinks and munchies stocked. No, they‚Äôre not serving sandwiches ‚Äî not a single Maple Leaf I‚Äôve been to does that. However, they have some nice soups, hummus, salsa, tahini/yogurt, two different salads, edamame and cookies. Thanks to Maria and Alexis for making travel that much easier!< /Review>

< Review>
Small lounge, there‚Äôs not enough seating and it‚Äôs cramped.. sitting areas so close to one another that you hear all the neighbors conversations. Food selection limited, and ran out 2.5 hours before lounge closed. Only apples available as fruit option. Departure screen at back hidden behind some decorative wall, so you have to get up and walk all the way across the lounge to see info. I literally scraped the dish to get the stuff that‚Äôs in my picture.</Review>

<user_name>Derek Chiu< /user_name><date>1576460846166</date><rating>4</rating>< Text>
The old MLL in Terminal 2 was much roomier and spacious.  This one is small and cramped.  The elevator up to the lounge level is very slow and is often crowded.  The lounge is still a good place to relax, grab a quick bite, a beverage and get some work done in a quiet place.  It can be crowded at times but the majority of my flights out of Terminal 6 is at 6:20am for the LAX to YVR flight so there are few of us in the lounge at that time.</Text>

<Review>Arrived at the lounge at 8am and it was not very busy.  The pros are there are many coffee choices, some juices, and limited fruit.  What I qas mot impressed with the choices of food, there was not much to tie you over.  There were limited newspapers and magazines, so after an hour we had to leave to grab food for our connecting flight.  The Air Canada lounge at YYZ offers a lot more options, food and drinks wise and many magazines to pass the time.  This was a stark contrast and not a lot of consistency.  Would have loved to stay longer, cleaner bathrooms and relatively peaceful.  The staff were very good at LAX lounge.  Always coming around to offer to take things away, they were very pleasant.</Review>< Pics>

< Review>
I would say that of all of the fast food restaurants that serve hamburgers in this country, Fatburger is the best. Everything about it tastes great and that make it all fresh, from scratch, right there in front of you. The only downside is it takes time to cook a hamburger correctly, so these hamburgers are not ready in 1 and 1/2 minutes. It usually takes about 7 or 8 minutes and that for some reason just seems weird because we are also used to food being ready in 30 seconds. They are doing it the right way and the quality shows!< /Review>

< text>
This is not my first time to this Fatburger location. The first time being there was meh. The food was amazing, don't get me wrong. There was absolutely nothing wrong with the food. The service on the other hand was subpar. So I did leave a 1 or 2 star review for that visit. This time, they got it right. The cashier was helpful and when my vegan family went up to order, the cashier knew exactly what they meant when they said Impossible burger and vegan cheese. Gonna come back again especially since it's pretty close to Universal Studios. The food here definitely beats the food on the City Walk and it's a hell of a lot cheaper too. üòÉ<//text>

<rating>5</rating><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< text>
I love Fatburger! I love it better than the other two competitors In-N-Out and Tommy's, Fatburger is the place where else can you get your fat better made the way you want it charbroiled or grilled they even have a king-size Fatburger you literally haven't made to your liking they'll even put egg in it if you want. And you got a choice of onion rings skinny fries and fat fries and you can even have them topped with chili and cheese if you'd like. If you have never tried Fatburger please give it a try you will fall in love with it. Oh! I almost forgot their milkshakes are made with real ice cream on-the-spot and they even have a jukebox to listen good old-fashioned rock and roll and oldies while you're eating your Fatburger! Now the other two competitors cannot top that at all!< /text>

< user_name>
Ryan P. Nakamoto<//user_name>
< Time>
1420928773280</Time>
<rate>1<//rate>< review>
*DO NOT USE THIS MOVING COMPANY*
I moved to San Diego to work a tech company here and the company arranged for moving logistics and I thought it would be hassle-free.  I couldn't have been more wrong.  I would have rather moved things myself and traded some sweat for damages and missing property.
1- Every piece of glossed wood furniture I have was scratched noticeably (or looked more like it was gouged in squiggly lines and circles).  I get that some wear and tear is inevitable when moving things, but I noticed that none of this furniture was covered at all, not even with paper or saran wrap.  It just came out of the truck unprotected.  I had one medium coffee table, a medium side table, 2 small stands, a kitchen table and computer desk.
2- I'm missing some smaller mobile items that I didn't notice was missing until later. Namely a new skateboard and quality work/utility gloves.  They happened to be in the same area in my old apartment and I've now noticed they've gone missing.
3- They take inventory of what they've packed, and you sign off on it.  They're in a hurry to get out of there after packing up and so you need to go through 4-8 pages of logged inventory and quickly see if anything is missing.  You can probably take your time and go through it meticulously if you remember every single item you've had packed, but they let it be known they are in a hurry.  Also sometimes a line item will be something like "various kitchenware", so not everything is specified.
4- On unpack you have to try to note damages while they are moving things in.  It's also not that pleasant whenever you note on the forms any damages and the mover always asks, "is there a problem, bro?" when you do so.  I listed the shattered glass lamp that they took with them, as well as my dented metal trash can and ripped leather recliner, etc. in my damages form, but not the wood furniture.  I should have listed the latter, that's my own fault, but I got tired of the stress from dealing with this stuff.  I also didn't notice my new skateboard and gloves were missing until later.

I can't really go back and fix this frustrating experience, but if I knew this was how it would go down I would have gone out of my way to either move myself, or research another company that might care a little bit about my belongings and respect my property.

I can buy a new skateboard and gloves for about $200-220 and just accept that my furniture is scratched, but I shouldn't have to.  And you shouldn't either.   So either be absolutely meticulous with the paperwork for your moved items and note all damages and missing items, or find another alternative.  I really wish I had...</review>

< Text>
Problem 1: WRONG DELIVERY (A container for Sydney was delivered to HK; the other container for HK is still on the way to Sydney. Sullivan mixed them up in US)
Problem 2: BAD ATTITUDE EVEN AFTER MAKING THIS TERRIBLE FAULT (My impression is that Sullivan does not care about its customers even this situation!!)
-> DO NOT BE FOOLED INTO THINKING SULLIVAN WILL TAKE CARE OF YOU OR YOUR BELONGINGS WELL AFTER YOU HAVE AN INSPECTION - IT WILL HAVE TWO FACES ONCE YOU SIGNED THE CONTRACT.
Problem 3: HIDDEN COSTS / OWN INTERPRETATION REGARDLESS OF THE CONTRACT

Here are the details.
Problem 1: [WRONG DELIVERY] Our family have two containers: one for Hong Kong, and the other for Sydney, Australia. The company mixed up our two containers in US. In HK, we received the container supposed to be delivered to Sydney (What a surprise!), and the other one supposed to be delivered to HK is still on the way to Sydney. You can imagine how your life will be without your belongings. Of course, the expected delivery date is not guaranteed one, so you might expect a certain level of inconvenience when you move to other places. However, this is different story. Can you do this for two months due to the moving company‚Äôs fault? We are having very difficult times living without our personal effects. We had to buy redundant items that we should have received already in HK, and had to go out for lunch or dinner more frequently than we usually do. We are going to file an inconvenience claim. In sum, your containers could be found in other places.
Problem 2: [BAD ATTITUDE] We were completely shocked in HK due to the wrong delivery. We asked this company about its detailed plan of actions to deal with its fault. However, we didn‚Äôt get any detailed plans (we got just general short email, that is it). So, we itemized each question to help address this issue, but AFTER TWO WEEKS we DIDN‚ÄôT GET ANY SINGLE RESPONSE. We are the one who called the local moving company to find out what is going on, and Sullivan didn‚Äôt respond it. This is what you are going to get from Sullivan if you sign the contract. Be careful. Sullivan does not respect its customers. Isn‚Äôt it this company‚Äôs responsibility to update relevant information to customers to fix this problem? This is obviously Sullivan‚Äôs mistakes, but we felt that this company is acting as if there isn‚Äôt anything happened. When the company inspect your house, you might think that this company will take care of you and your belongings very well. This was same for us. But, DO NOT BE FOOLED. Once you sign the contract, they won‚Äôt. Besides this absurd situation, the company has not been responsive / not kept its promise: Sullivan told us that we would get a regular (say weekly) updates about our shipment, but it never happened. This is what this company is. You will spend a lot of time and efforts if you work with this company.
Problem 3: [HIDDEN COSTS / OWN INTERPRETATION REGARDLESS OF THE CONTRACT]
I was informed that I need to pay extra delivery charges because my apartment is on 4th floor. I didn‚Äôt quite understand why this is the case. See the below my contract with the company.
"Rate Includes: Dedicated move manager from door to door, ... , normal access loading at residence, ... , complete delivery to residence with normal access, ..." Also, "Rate excludes: ... charges relating to limited access delivery (..., 3rd floor or higher with NO elevator use, ...)‚Äù
My apartment has an elevator, and the local moving company can use this elevator. Even though the contract says ‚Äú3rd floor or higher with NO elevator use‚Äù will be charged for extra costs, Sullivan replied to me saying that ‚Äúthat is not how it is interpreted‚Äù. I was shocked again. The funny thing is that our family has the same, but separate contract for HK moving. Terms in the contract regarding rates are exactly the same with the contract for Sydney. But, when this company wrongly delivered Sydney stuffs to HK, they didn‚Äôt charge any extra costs for delivery even though our apartment in HK is located in 15th floor.<//Text>

< Review>
DONT COME HERE

What I asked for and what I got were two different things. I did ask for a different shape than the reference photo, but that's about it. I went in at 2pm, and I left two and a half hours later and not even with something I was proud of. I'll admit it seemed like the stylist was trying, but I would rather them have told me that they couldn't do it.

Not only did she use a SHARPIE MARKER against my wishes (I told them when they put the clear coat on that it would bleed out purple and be a mess, and that's exactly what happened) but when she had to re-do them more than 3 times they tried to pin it on me. Saying that "well if you bought gel that wouldn't happen",  but other places do it fine ü§î, but other places also dont use sharpies on NAILS. Even then, at one point I TOOK THE SHARPIE AND DID IT MYSELF. It's bad enough you're using a tool against my wishes but if you're not able to do the design JUST TELL ME.

Look, I don't like writing reviews like this, BUT I had a bad experience and I have to share it here because I never received a customer survey.

I came here for routine maintenance last week and was pretty disappointed with the level of service provided. I had to leave my car for a couple days (bummer), but I was offered a rental car (nice!). Unfortunately, I was not told the hours of the rental car place (Hertz), which closed before I arrived after work. (They're open 9-5 M-F, 9-12p Saturday btw) Since the rental car agency was only open at times when I would be at work, I was unable to rent a car. I ended up taking rideshares at my own expense while my car was in the shop.

I felt like while my technician was courteous, he couldn't wait to get me off the phone, and I never saw or spoke with him again after my car was ready to be picked up. I tried calling him back to tell him the rental car situation but he did not return my call, instead he sent me a text saying I could drop off the rental car at the shop. This was frustrating because I spent a lot of money here. The least they could do was acknowledge my frustration.

I'm giving two stars because I was able to use a 15% off discount I saw on the website, which saved me a couple hundred dollars. But I still paid through the nose to get my car serviced. <Review>Beyond amazing! My husband and I have been shopping for a used 4Runner for about 3 months or so. I saw Toyota of Glendale had a 4Runner that we loved; why? Because of the miles on the vehicle, the condition, and price. My husband and I have been shopping and visited a couple of dealerships before we head here. We drove from Orange County to Glendale to look, not acknowledging that we would make a purchase.

DJ W., sales rep, approached us. He greeted us and began helping us locate the vehicle. After finding the car, checking it out, I decided to do a test drive. I fell in love with it! But my husband and I had some concerns with moving forward with the vehicle since we are still paying for a Jeep Renegade and wanted to make a trade-in; we were hesitant because the previous dealership has let us down with a high down payment, high interest rate and low trade-in value.

DJ W. Went to informed Arthur K. we are interested. We discussed our situation and how we didn't want to do a credit check yet. We wanted to know what options were, giving the fact we know we had to do a credit check to be more realistic. Arthur K. Guaranteed me that he would be able to get a deal for us that day. No matter what obstacle they were facing with our finances and credit check.

After viewing our options, we decided to move forward with the purchase. Arthur K and DJ W. Worked hard on our approval, took a couple of tries to get the right bank to take accept the new car loan. I was amazed when Arthur K came back and told us he got us a sweet deal. We had a low out-of-pocket deposit with low interest; only my husband applied, no co-signer for the loan's approval.

I was very frustrated and opposed to dealerships because having greedy sales rep with sales manager be pushy and not take the time to help their customers. When my husband and I saw how they were working with us and not being pessimistic about what we desire, I felt confident purchasing the 4Runner from this dealership. The whole time we were there, I never heard DJ W. or Arthur K said NO; it was always a yes or let me see what I can do. I value their time, professionalism, work ethic, and communication. They worked with my husband and me. That's what I admire.

When it came to finalizing our purchase, we met with Freddy M, the finance manager. He was very kind and patient. He heard us out, answered our questions, and allowed us to review each document that was being signed. He wasn't pushy or hurrying us up; even tho that day was busy. Freddy M was very friendly and helpful. Overall they were all so sweet, generous, and kind. They are there to help and get what is comfortable for you and provide excellent customer service. During this time, I tried calling Paul many times to know the status of my car, and I saw him ignore the phone and letting it go to voicemail. After I received my car, I noticed that the car is extremely dirty and messy from the inside, moreover the RADIO WAS BROKEN. Paul tried to fix it, but it didn't work. <user>101155863122177382636< /user><Name>Dann O'Quinn</Name><time>1425429404115<//time><rating>5<//rating>< review>
Henry Saunders, the service writer is the best service guy I've ever had. Conscientious, kept me up to date on the progress and didn't recommend things to be done that were in good shape - a MAJOR problem I had with North Hollywood Toyota.
I recently had a very elusive electrical problem in my 2000 Tacoma. An on and off misfire that was hard to track down. Before I took it to Glendale Toyota I had an independent change the plugs, then the plug wires and coils. Still misfired. At this point I figured I better take this problem to someone who knows only Toyotas. I went online, checked out reviews on the dealers in my area and only Glendale had good reviews. I took it in on Monday morning and got Henry. first off they found out that the indie guy had put the wrong plugs in. They corrected that and then went on the hunt for the electrical problem. They worked with it until they managed to get a code. The code traced back to an injector. They corrected the problem and returned my truck in great working order. I couldn't be happier. Can't go wrong with Henry, best service writer ever!<//review>

<Review>I had such a wonderful experience leasing my car through Toyota of Glendale! I specifically dealt with Mario (Sales) and Beto (Finance) and they were super friendly, straight-forward, transparent and a pleasure to do business with. I am not an easy person to please when it comes to car shopping because I am very picky when it comes to service (I have a background in the service industry and sales) and price (I do a lot of research and have bargained with numerous dealerships for previous purchases).

To give you an idea of how my experience went down, here is the background story: Around Xmas, I decided that I wanted to lease a 2017 Prius from a dealership in LA so I called 8 different dealerships and asked for their most competitive pricing. What really stood out about the response I received from Toyota of Glendale (I cannot remember the name of the woman who helped me over the phone, I am sorry!), was that on our very first call, they asked me what I wanted to pay and then went to their manager and got me their very best pricing. It was super simple and there was no sales-y sliminess involved. I felt they were honest in that they had given me their best and I also confirmed it. The reason why I know that it was absolutely their very best pricing is because I called all the other dealerships back who I had been on the phone with multiple times in negotiation and no one would come back with a price that was lower than Toyota of Glendale.

I immediately set up an appointment and headed in to lease my new Prius. That's where I met Mario. Mario is a super sweet, super knowledgeable salesman who let me see everything they had available cracked funny jokes with me while I was in the shopping process. I felt he was super approachable and again, I did not get a weird/slimy sales-y vibe that I have so frequently encountered with car salesmen.

After doing paperwork and deciding on my specific car, I was then passed along to Beto who works in finance. He was also a super friendly guy who explained the whole process of leasing to me and was able to get me a stellar deal on the extra vehicle coverage. He made a long, often painful process light-hearted and fun.

Overall, I really enjoyed leasing my 2017 Prius from Toyota of Glendale. I will definitely be going back there for service and any future call leasing or purchases.
